-- Mexico Stocks: OHL Mexico, Asur, Televisa Shares Are Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-05-14T21:14:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/mexico-stocks-ohl-mexico-asur-televisa-shares-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index fell 1.4 percent to 38,352.11.  OHL Mexico SAB (OHLMEX*)  , the Mexican unit of Spanish
construction company  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL) , tumbled 6.7
percent to 17.40 pesos. It has declined 14 percent since the end
of trading on May 10, when OHL Mexico said in a filing to
Mexico’s stock exchange that the state of Puebla unilaterally
voided a concession with its unit Autovias Concesionadas OHL.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA*)  , the country’s biggest
construction company, tumbled 7.7 percent to 22.14 pesos.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB  (ASURB MM), the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, fell 2.2 percent to
102.66 pesos after subtracting a dividend paid out today.
Without the dividend effect, the shares would be up 1.2 percent,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Bolsa Mexicana de Valores SAB  (BOLSAA MM), the operator of
Mexico’s securities exchange, fell 5.5 percent to 26.14 pesos
after going ex-dividend. Without the dividend effect, the stock
would be down 1.3 percent, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
